ee?" Although he did not actually travel throughout Japan, he is known to have visited this shrine.</ref> The main tree is surrounded by five saplings; its trunk has a circumference of 13.1 meters and a height of 19 meters, and it is designated as a national {{ill|Natural Monument|ja|天然記念物|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Natural Monument|qq=}} under the name {{ill|Great Kozaki Kusunoki|ja|神崎の大クス|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Great Kozaki Kusunoki|qq=}}. The shrine grove, known as the "Kozaki Forest", is designated as a natural monument of Chiba Prefecture ({{ill|Natural Monuments of Chiba Prefecture|ja|千葉県指定文化財一覧#天然記念物|lt=Chiba Prefecture Natural Monuments|lt_ja=千葉県の天然記念物|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Natural Monuments of Chiba Prefecture|qq=}}).

[[File:Kōzaki-jinja_(Kōzaki,_Chiba)_12.jpg|thumb|right|230px|{{ill|Great Kozaki Kusunoki|ja|神崎の大クス|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Great Kozaki Kusunoki|qq=}}. Commonly known as the Nanjamonja tree.]]

The shrine has long received strong patronage from successive rulers, and it is said that during the {{ill|Sengoku period|ja|Sengoku period|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sengoku period|qq=}} it possessed shrine domains covering 700 {{ill|Town (unit)|ja|町|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Town (unit)|qq=}} ({{ill|Shrine domain|ja|寺社領|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shrine domain|qq=}}). During the {{ill|Edo period|ja|江戸時代|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Edo period|qq=}}, it held 20 koku of {{ill|Shuin land|ja|朱印地・黒印地|lt=Red Seal Land|lt_ja=朱印領|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shuin land|qq=}}, and the "Kōzaki Shrine Documents"—a collection of ancient manuscripts and illustrations passed down from the early {{ill|Kamakura period|ja|鎌倉時代|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamakura period|qq=}} to the {{ill|Muromachi period|ja|室町時代|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Muromachi period|qq=}}—is considered an extremely important historical source of the {{ill|Medieval|ja|中世|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Medieval|qq=}} period ({{ill|Historical source|ja|史料|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Historical source|qq=}}), having been designated as a tangible cultural property (ancient documents) of Chiba Prefecture ({{ill|Tangible Cultural Property (Ancient Documents) of Chiba Prefecture|ja|千葉県指定文化財一覧#古文書|lt=Chiba Prefecture Tangible Cultural Property (Ancient Documents)|lt_ja=千葉県の有形文化財（古文書）|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tangible Cultural Property (Ancient Documents) of Chiba Prefecture|qq=}}). Furthermore, the "Jinguji Documents" held by the former head temple ({{ill|Head temple|ja|別当寺|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Head temple|qq=}}) {{ill|Jinguji|ja|神宮寺 (千葉県神崎町)|lt=Jinguji|lt_ja=神宮寺|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jinguji|qq=}}, despite missing 60 out of 600 volumes of the {{ill|Mahaprajnaparamita Sutra|ja|大般若波羅蜜多経|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mahaprajnaparamita Sutra|qq=}}, are highly valued as a sutra transcription from the {{ill|Nanboku-chō period|ja|南北朝時代 (日本)|lt=Nanboku-chō period|lt_ja=南北朝期|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nanboku-chō period|qq=}}. The colophon ({{ill|Colophon|ja|奥書|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Colophon|qq=}}) reveals details about the temples ({{ill|Temple|ja|寺院|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Temple|qq=}}), monks ({{ill|Monk|ja|僧侶|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Monk|qq=}}), and the sphere of religious influence at that time, and it has also been designated as a tangible cultural property of Chiba Prefecture ({{ill|Tangible Cultural Property of Chiba Prefecture|ja|千葉県指定文化財一覧#古文書|lt=Chiba Prefecture Tangible Cultural Property|lt_ja=千葉県の有形文化財|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tangible Cultural Property of Chiba Prefecture|qq=}}).

== Transportation ==
* About a 20‐minute walk from {{ill|Narita Line|ja|成田線|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Narita Line|qq=}}{{ill|Shimōsa-Kozaki Station|ja|下総神崎駅|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shimōsa-Kozaki Station|qq=}}
* Near the south end of Kozaki Ōhashi on {{ill|National Route 356|ja|国道356号|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/National Route 356|qq=}} and {{ill|Ibaraki and Chiba Prefectural Road 107, Edosaki-Kozaki Line|ja|茨城県道・千葉県道107号江戸崎神崎線|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ibaraki and Chiba Prefectural Road 107, Edosaki-Kozaki Line|qq=}}

